======================================================================
STEP 2: Score 0 or n-1 => not in any 3-cycle (trivial)
======================================================================
This is trivially true:
  score 0: v loses to all, so v->x never happens => no cycle through v
  score n-1: v beats all, so x->v never happens => no cycle through v
Verification:
  n=5: violations = 0
  n=6: violations = 0
  n=7: violations = 0

======================================================================
STEP 3: v in no cycle => freed(w) can't span V\{w} for w != v
======================================================================
If v is in no 3-cycle, vertex v cannot appear in any cycle.
freed(w) uses only cycle vertices, so can't include v.
Thus freed(w) spans at most V\{v,w}, which has n-2 < n-1 vertices.
n=5 (exhaustive): no extreme-score vertices with freed sets
n=6 (exhaustive): no extreme-score vertices with freed sets
n=7 (sampled(10000)): no extreme-score vertices with freed sets
n=8 (sampled(3000)): no extreme-score vertices with freed sets

